            <head>"TO A BROWN BOY"</head>
            
            <lg>
               <l>That brown girl’s swagger gives a twitch</l>
               <l rend="i1">To beauty like a queen;</l>
               <l>Lad, never dam your body’s itch</l>
               <l rend="i1">When loveliness is seen.</l>
            </lg>

            <lg>
               <l>For there is ample room for bliss</l>
               <l rend="i1">In pride in clean, brown limbs,</l>
               <l>And lips know better how to kiss .</l>
               <l rend="i1">Than how to raise white hymns.</l>
            </lg>
            
            <lg>
               <l>And when your body’s death gives birth</l>
               <l rend="i1">To soil for spring to crown,</l>
               <l>Men will not ask if that rare earth</l>
               <l rend="i1">Was white flesh once, or brown.</l>
            </lg>

            <byline>-Countée Cullen</byline>
         </div>
      </body>
